post_text:
Hello,

We had an unexpectedly high number of people who wanted to attend the virtual Community Meeting last evening. Apparently anyone who tried to enter the meeting after we had 100 participants was unable to attend.

I apologize for the inconvenience, and will repeat the meeting next Tuesday at 6pm. Check back here for the link which we'll post soon.

Thanks to everyone who was able to attend for your interest and thoughtful comments.

Stay safe,
Mr. Newman

Shout out to the OUSD staff. These are just some of the learning materials we're sending out to students! Teachers, instructional aides, office staff and maintenance staff all pitching in to keep our kids learning...

post_text: Our FFA Students need your assistance. Agriculture students raise animals every year to learn about the industry, and for the experience of developing responsiblity through animal care & feeding. They usually recoup their investment because prices at the Fair sale are generally higher than market prices. Without the Fair sale, many of our students would take significant financial losses. Please see the attached letter and help if you are able. Thank you.

The Orland volunteer Fire department is asking for dontations to help those who have lost everything in the Camp fire. There is currently a great need for the following items:

Clothing
Blankets
Pillows
Feminine hygiene products
Toiletries

All donations can be dropped off at the Orland fire department located at 810 5th street next to ACE hardware. Every little bit helps, Thanks.
